The insurance argument is a loophole people use when they want to make someone else stop doing something that they think is wrong.   Also Insurance companies will raise premiums for any reason possible, however petty. <br>
<br>
Like if you live in a perfect neighborhood that hasn't had a car accident in 50 years, and some kid gets dents the fender of your parked car with his BMX, insurance companies can label you're entire neighborhood a high risk zone and raise everyones premiums as if it were a ghetto.  Why? becasue they can and they are greedy.<br>
<br>
Insurance companies have the 2nd highest profit margin of any industry in the world, next to banks.  Don't blame smokers for their greed.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
